.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH package 1  "package " 
.SH NAME
package \- Manage locally installed collection packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpackage\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage locally installed collection packages
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
package\-search(1)
List locally installed packages, optionally filtering by text
.TP
package\-info(1)
Show a collection manifest
.TP
package\-install(1)
Verify, stage, and atomically install a collection version
.TP
package\-upgrade(1)
Install a newer collection manifest version
.TP
package\-remove(1)
Remove a non\-current installed collection version
.TP
package\-verify(1)
Verify an installed collection version against its manifest
.TP
package\-list(1)
List locally installed collections
.TP
package\-versions(1)
List installed versions for a collection
.TP
package\-switch(1)
Switch the active installed collection version
.TP
package\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
